## ── CONFIGURE ── Cockpit topology

This section is regenerated by `/setup-e2e-cockpit` once the app topology is discovered.
Until then, the generic windows below apply (see `tmux-cockpit.sh`).

| tmux window   | Role |
|---------------|------|
| `overseer`    | Orchestrates workers, reads results, delegates |
| `k8s-logs`    | Live log tails from the app's backend/services |
| `k8s-pf`      | Port-forward → `localhost:@@BACKEND_PORT@@` — must stay alive |
| `chromium`    | Playwright browser (CDP) |
| `worker-test` | E2E Test Operator — `e2e-operator` skill |
| `worker-dev`  | Developer — `worker-dev` skill |
| `worker-fix`  | Troubleshooter — `worker-fix` skill |

The **local dev cockpit** (`tmux-cockpit-local.sh`) replaces the remote log/port-forward
windows with a `backend` window running the app locally on `:@@BACKEND_PORT@@`.

---

## ── CONFIGURE ── Connection

| Resource | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Frontend | `http://localhost:@@FRONTEND_PORT@@` |
| Backend  | `http://localhost:@@BACKEND_PORT@@` |
| Health check | `curl -sk http://localhost:@@BACKEND_PORT@@@@HEALTH_PATH@@` |

